{"comments":"WebGL2 Rendering Target\n\nRenders DrawCommands via WebGL2 for GPU-accelerated graphics.\nThis is the fallback when WebGPU is not available.\n\n## Browser Support\n\nWebGL2 is supported on:\n- iOS Safari 15+ (2021)\n- Android Chrome 58+ (2017)\n- Desktop Chrome 56+ (2017)\n- Firefox 51+ (2017)\n- Edge 79+ (2020)\n\n## Performance Characteristics\n\nWebGL2 is true GPU rendering with:\n- Programmable shaders (GLSL ES 3.0)\n- Instanced rendering for particles\n- Texture atlases for text\n- Hardware anti-aliasing\n\nGood for:\n- 10,000+ particles\n- Complex effects (blur, glow)\n- Smooth animations at 60fps\n\n## Architecture\n\nDrawCommands are batched by type and rendered in passes:\n1. Opaque geometry (front-to-back)\n2. Transparent geometry (back-to-front)\n3. Post-processing effects\n\n## Usage\n\n```purescript\nimport Hydrogen.Target.WebGL as WebGL\nimport Hydrogen.GPU.Flatten as Flatten\n\nrenderWithWebGL :: Element Msg -> Effect Unit\nrenderWithWebGL element = do\n  ctx <- WebGL.getContext \"my-canvas\"\n  case ctx of\n    Left err -> Console.log err\n    Right gl -> do\n      let result = Flatten.flatten element\n      WebGL.render gl result.commands\n```\n","declarations":[{"children":[],"comments":"Opaque WebGL2 rendering context.\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"data","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[118,41],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Target/WebGL.purs","start":[118,1]},"title":"WebGLContext"},{"children":[],"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Effect"],"Effect"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["